I like this approach because it feels safer- you don’t need to think to cancel an out-of-control robot action (and I have, a few days ago, used this benefit). Basically acts like a dead person’s switch.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-02-02T01:46:03.833Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":66,"readers_count":65,"score":38.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":484739,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pattern-on-the-fly-override","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":58301,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"coder in the corner"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pattern-on-the-fly-override/484739/2","custom_user_title":"coder in the corner","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3499667,"name":"Andy Hegemann","username":"Andy_H","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/779978/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-02T02:05:09.663Z","cooked":"<p>You can also take it one step further and add a <code>.and()</code> with a Trigger to the whileHeld. We are using this to allow our driver to take control of the movement at any time without having to wait for the operator to stop the path command</p>
<p>Here’s a snipbit of our <a href="https://github.com/CSE-WestHS/6317-2024-Reefscape/blob/e5dc122bf6d6f871860af7ee55e236e2f03f8993/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java#L237" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">RobotContainer.java</a> that controls that logic</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  private final Trigger leftXTrigger =
      new Trigger(() -&gt; (Math.abs(driverController.getLeftX())) &gt; DriveCommands.DEADBAND);
  private final Trigger leftYTrigger =
      new Trigger(() -&gt; (Math.abs(driverController.getLeftY())) &gt; DriveCommands.DEADBAND);
  private final Trigger rightXTrigger =
      new Trigger(() -&gt; (Math.abs(driverController.getRightX())) &gt; DriveCommands.DEADBAND);
  private final Trigger driverInputTrigger =
      new Trigger(
          () -&gt;  leftXTrigger.getAsBoolean()
                  || leftYTrigger.getAsBoolean()
                  || rightXTrigger.getAsBoolean());
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">OperatorController.y()
        .and(driverInputTrigger.negate())
        .whileTrue(drive.generatePath(new Pose2d(3.589, 5.334, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(-128.721))));
</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-02-02T02:05:09.663Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":55,"readers_count":54,"score":56.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":484739,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pattern-on-the-fly-override","display_username":"Andy Hegemann","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/CSE-WestHS/6317-2024-Reefscape/blob/e5dc122bf6d6f871860af7ee55e236e2f03f8993/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java#L237","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"6317-2024-Reefscape/src/main/java/frc/robot/RobotContainer.java at e5dc122bf6d6f871860af7ee55e236e2f03f8993 · CSE-WestHS/6317-2024-Reefscape · GitHub","clicks":10}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":58301,"username":"LHACK4142","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/lhack4142/{size}/196107_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62983,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pattern-on-the-fly-override/484739/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true}],"stream":[3499586,3499640,3499667]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,252]],"suggested_topics":[{"fancy_title":"Kraken x60 noise","id":493542,"title":"Kraken x60 noise","slug":"kraken-x60-noise","posts_count":5,"reply